Program: The Forum
Title: Advances in Bioengineering
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03lqvjc
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 16 Mar 2016
Bridget Kendall talks to three pioneers who are pushing the boundaries of what is possible at the interface between engineering, biology and medicine: John Rogers makes electronics which dissolve when they have done their job, Magnus Berggren grows circuits inside plants and Hadyn Parry is using a harmless protein to wipe out dangerous disease carriers. Picture: A rose attached to an electronic apparatus. (Credit: Eliot Gomez) Show less